# Application-specific Kconfig. Symbols defined here are layered on top of the
# normal Zephyr tree, which is pulled in by the trailing source line.

config APP_SPEAKER
	bool "Speaker tone shell command (LEDC PWM)"
	depends on PWM && SHELL
	help
	  Drive the speaker (XIAO header D3 / GPIO21) with a hardware LEDC PWM
	  channel: a 50% square wave at the requested frequency, generated by the
	  peripheral with no CPU work. Registers a "tone <centi-hz> <ms>" shell
	  command. The pin and channel are set in app.overlay.

config APP_MOTOR
	bool "A4988 stepper control with motor shell commands"
	depends on GPIO && PWM && SHELL
	help
	  Wire the A4988 stepper driver to the XIAO header and expose a "motor"
	  shell command group for bench debugging. STEP is D0 / GPIO0 / LEDC
	  channel 0 (the step pulse train), DIR is D1 / GPIO1, and EN is D2 /
	  GPIO2 (active-low). The pins are set in app.overlay. See DESIGN.md.

config APP_ANTENNA
	bool "Power the RF switch and select the onboard antenna"
	depends on GPIO
	help
	  The XIAO ESP32-C6 routes both the onboard antenna and the U.FL
	  connector through an RF switch (enable GPIO3, select GPIO14). A default
	  build leaves the switch unpowered, so the radio runs on a degraded
	  leakage path. This drives GPIO3 to power the switch and GPIO14 to select
	  the onboard antenna, reusing the board's rf_switch devicetree node. No
	  effect unless the radio is used. See docs/LOG.md [antenna].

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
